Detailed Description

Listener for Geocoding and reverse Geocoding lookups. The abstract functions are callback functions that are called as a response to the respective asynchronous call in LocationInterface.

Create a subclass and implement the callbacks. Then pass a pointer to this class to the appropriate Geocoding request.

The error function, declared in the super class Listener, will be called for all requests that returns with an error. The status code can be either from the StatusCode enumeration or from RouteStatusCode enumeration.
